#using the LactoRNAseqCountFile_manuscript.csv file from the Schalich et. al paper (https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/microbiology/articles/10.3389/fmicb.2022.1051310/full) to design an RNA seq analysis protocol
#File formats
#	• Count File:
#		○ Gene IDs are leftmost column, each gene has its own row, there are no duplicates
#		○ Individual samples are the other columns with their SampleID being in row 1, and gene counts are in the following rows
# • Metadata File:
#		○ Row 1 contains variable names (treatment/condition/cell type/etc)
#		○ Column 1 contains Sample IDs. Column 2 contains SampleIDs again under variable name (SampleIDs)
#		○ Samples are rows, so each sample's unique conditions are then placed in its row under the corresponding variable name


